SIMPLE: peri
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peri-
<hw>Per"i-</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧r"⟦icr⟧-)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>peri`</grk>,
prep.]</ety> <def>A prefix used to signify <sig>around</sig>,
<sig>by</sig>, <sig>near</sig>, <sig>over</sig>, <sig>beyond</sig>, or
to give an <xex>intensive</xex> sense; <as>as, <ex>peri</ex>meter, the
measure around; <ex>peri</ex>gee, point near the earth;
<ex>peri</ex>ergy, work beyond what is needed; <ex>peri</ex>spherical,
quite spherical.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peri</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Peri
<hw>Pe"ri</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧"r⟦icr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Peris</plw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧"r⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Per. <ets>per⟦imac⟧</ets> a female genus, a fairy.]</ety>
<fld>(Persian Myth.)</fld> <def>An imaginary being, male or female, like
an elf or fairy, represented as a descendant of fallen angels, excluded
from paradise till penance is accomplished.</def>
<rj><au>Moore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1066 --></p>

<p><ent>Periagua</ent>⟦br⟧
